</site><head title="General Type| step"/><section title="Description"><b>A step is a single command to be executed by webtest.</b><pre>
	<b>Test steps are grouped into three major categories:</b>
	<dl>
		<li>
			<dt>Action</dt>
			<dd>Issue an HTTP request and store the result, e.g. invoke the URL
				"http://www.seibertec.ch/wiki".</dd>
		</li>
		<li>
			<dt>Verification</dt>
			<dd>Verify the correctness of the latest result, e.g. ensure
				that a particular text string occurs in the page title.</dd>
		</li>
		<li>
			<dt>Manipulation</dt>
			<dd>Prepare the next request, e.g. by setting parameter values.</dd>
		</li>
	</dl>
</pre></section><section title="Usage"><b><stepref name="antWrapper"/>, <stepref name="applyFilters"/>, <stepref name="expectDialogs"/>, <stepref name="group"/>, <stepref name="ifStep"/>, <stepref name="not"/>, <stepref name="repeat"/>, <stepref name="reportSite"/>, <stepref name="retry"/>, <stepref name="selectWebClient"/>, <stepref name="steps"/>, <stepref name="storeDigest"/>, <stepref name="storeLength"/>, <stepref name="timedGroup"/>, <stepref name="verifyContent"/>.</b></section></manpage>